rx.observables
Class BlockingObservable<T>

java.lang.Object
  rx.Observable<T>
      rx.observables.BlockingObservable<T>
Type Parameters:
T - 
public class BlockingObservable<T>
extends Observable<T>

Extension of Observable that provides blocking operators.

Constructud via BlockingObservable.from(Observable) or Observable.toBlockingObservable()

forEach

public void forEach(Action1<T> onNext)
Invokes an action for each element in the observable sequence, and blocks until the sequence is terminated.

NOTE: This will block even if the Observable is asynchronous.

This is similar to Observable.subscribe(Observer) but blocks. Because it blocks it does not need the Observer.onCompleted() or Observer.onError(Exception) methods.

Parameters:
onNext - Action1
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if error occurs

forEach

public void forEach(java.lang.Object o)
Invokes an action for each element in the observable sequence, and blocks until the sequence is terminated.

NOTE: This will block even if the Observable is asynchronous.

This is similar to Observable.subscribe(Observer) but blocks. Because it blocks it does not need the Observer.onCompleted() or Observer.onError(Exception) methods.

Parameters:
o - onNext action
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if error occurs
